s-standard.com/article/opinion/new-multilateralism-with-old-paradigms-120041601884_1.html" target="_blank">https://www.business-standard.com/article/opinion/new-multilateralism-with-old-paradigms-120041601884_1.html</a>.&nbsp;</div></li><li><span>6</span><div>King, David, Daniel Schrag, Zhou Dadi, Qi Ye, and Arunabha Ghosh.&nbsp;<em>Climate Change: A Risk Assessment.</em>&nbsp;London: UK Foreign and Commonwealth Office, 2015; see also&nbsp;Corcoran, Katherine. ‘Food Prices Soaring Worldwide.’&nbsp;<em>Associated Press</em>, March 24, 2008. Accessed May 21, 2020.&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.agriculturedefensecoalition.org/sites/default/files/file/agriculture/3M_2008_Food_Worldwide_Shortages_High_Prices_March_2008_AP_Agriculture_Lands_Forests_Used_for_Ethanol_Disaster.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.agriculturedefensecoalition.org/sites/default/files/file/agriculture/3M_2008_Food_Worldwide_Shortages_High_Prices_March_2008_AP_Agriculture_Lands_Forests_Used_for_Ethanol_Disaster.pdf</a>.</div></li><li><span>7</span><div>Madge, Grahame. “New global record ‘likely’ within five years.”&nbsp;<em>Met Office</em>, last modified January 30, 2020. Accessed May 21, 2020.&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/about-us/press-office/news/weather-and-climate/2020/decadal-forecast-2020" target="_blank">https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/about-us/press-office/news/weather-and-climate/2020/decadal-forecast-2020</a>; see also Mead, Leila. “WMO Reports on 2019’s High-Impact Climate Events.”&nbsp;<em>IISD</em>, Last modified March 12, 2020. Accessed May 21, 2020.&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://sdg.iisd.org/news/wmo-reports-on-2019s-high-impact-climate-events/" target="_blank">https://sdg.iisd.org/news/wmo-reports-on-2019s-high-impact-climate-events/</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div></li><li><span>8</span><div>Watkins, Kevin et al.&nbsp;<em>Beyond scarcity: Power, poverty and the global water crisis: Human Development Report 2006.</em>